  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0b9a\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0bb2\u0bb5\u0bc8 \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Plan to control paper costs",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Ministry of Public Administration, Home Affairs, Provincial Councils and Local Government has decided to save significant amount of money every year.",
        "Accordingly, the Ministry has decided to reduce the 4 page application form which is larger than the A4 size used by government officials to apply for foreign leave to 2 pages on A4 paper.",
        "Secretary of the Ministry MMBK said that this matter will be implemented based on the advice of the Prime Minister Dinesh Gunawardena as the Minister of State. Mayatunne said.",
        "He also mentioned that around 50 percent of the paper cost for the application form can be saved.",
        "He also said that since the number of government employees who apply to go abroad annually is more than one lakh, the government can save paper and money.",
        "It has been informed that all the matters mentioned in the existing application form have been included in the new form and the applications have been sent to the Government Printing Department for printing."
      ],
